<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="495" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1585,1863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="495">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1729,1755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="495">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Novaes &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2014" box="[323,573,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mineira">
<emphasis box="[323,573,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="495">Anacroneuria mineira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected at Serra dos Pireneus and is a new record for the 
<collectingRegion box="[1304,1433,1729,1755]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="8" pageNumber="495">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. This species was originally described at Serra do Cipó, 
<collectingRegion box="[766,972,1765,1791]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="8" pageNumber="495">Minas Gerais state</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C." box="[986,1250,1765,1791]" pageId="8" pageNumber="495" pagination="433 - 442" refId="ref9666" refString="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C. (2014 c) Plecoptera from Minas Gerais State, southeastern Brazil. Zootaxa, 3856 (3), 433 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3856.3.8" type="journal article" year="2014">Novaes &amp; Bispo 2014c</bibRefCitation>
), and the present study now expands the distribution to Central 
<collectingCountry box="[660,732,1801,1827]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="495">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The specimens studied herein vary in size (anterior wing 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="495" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="11.0">11-15 mm</quantity>
) and are smaller than the 
<typeStatus box="[486,587,1837,1863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="495">holotype</typeStatus>
, which has an anterior wing around 
<quantity box="[993,1072,1837,1863]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="495" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C." box="[1086,1353,1837,1863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="495" pagination="433 - 442" refId="ref9666" refString="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C. (2014 c) Plecoptera from Minas Gerais State, southeastern Brazil. Zootaxa, 3856 (3), 433 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3856.3.8" type="journal article" year="2014">Novaes &amp; Bispo 2014c</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
